10 six months from the date of original application and desires to take
11 additional tests, the applicant shall file an application for reexamination
12 upon a form furnished by the division, which shall be accompanied by a
13 reexamination fee of $3, except that any applicant who fails to pass the
14 written or driving portion of an examination four times within a six-month
15 period, shall be required to wait a period of six months from the date of the
16 last failed examination before additional examinations may be given.
17 Upon the filing of such application and the payment of such reexamination
18 fee, the applicant shall be entitled to reexamination in like manner and
19 subject to the additional fees and time limitation as provided for
20 examination on an original application. If the applicant passes the
21 reexamination, the applicant shall be issued the classified driver's license
22 for which the applicant originally applied, which license shall be issued to
23 expire as if the applicant had passed the original examination.
24 (2) Applicants for class M licenses who have completed prior
25 motorcycle safety training in accordance with department of defense
26 instruction 6055.04 (DoDI 6055.04) or the motorcycle safety foundation
27 are not required to complete further written and driving testing pursuant to
28 paragraph (1). An applicant seeking exemption from the written and
29 driving tests pursuant to this paragraph shall provide a copy of the
30 motorcycle safety foundation completion form to the division prior to
31 receiving a class M license.
32 (3) On and after January 1, 2017, an applicant for a class M license
33 who passes a driving examination on a three-wheeled motorcycle that is
34 not an autocycle shall have a restriction placed on such applicant's license
35 limiting the applicant to the operation of a registered three-wheeled
36 motorcycle. An applicant for a class M license who passes a driving
37 examination on a two-wheeled motorcycle may operate any registered
38 two-wheeled or three-wheeled motorcycle. The driving examination
39 required by this paragraph shall be administered by the division, by the
40 department of defense or as part of a curriculum recognized by the
41 motorcycle safety foundation.
42 (b) (1) For the purposes of obtaining any driver's license or
43 instruction permit, an applicant shall submit, with the application, proof of

