1 age and proof of identity as the division may require. The applicant also
2 shall provide a photo identity document, except that a non-photo identity
3 document is acceptable if it includes both the applicant's full legal name
4 and date of birth, and documentation showing the applicant's name, the
5 applicant's address of principal residence and the applicant's social security
6 number. The applicant's social security number shall remain confidential
7 and shall not be disclosed, except as provided pursuant to K.S.A. 74-2012,
8 and amendments thereto. If the applicant does not have a social security
9 number, the applicant shall provide proof of lawful presence and Kansas
10 residency. The division shall assign a distinguishing number to the license
11 or permit.
12 (2) The division shall not issue any driver's license or instruction
13 permit to any person who fails to provide proof that the person is lawfully
14 present in the United States. Before issuing a driver's license or instruction
15 permit to a person, the division shall require valid documentary evidence
16 that the applicant: (A) Is a citizen or national of the United States; (B) is an
17 alien lawfully admitted for permanent or temporary residence in the
18 United States; (C) has conditional permanent resident status in the United
19 States; (D) has an approved application for asylum in the United States or
20 has entered into the United States in refugee status; (E) has a valid,
21 unexpired nonimmigrant visa or nonimmigrant visa status for entry into
22 the United States; (F) has a pending application for asylum in the United
23 States; (G) has a pending or approved application for temporary protected
24 status in the United States; (H) has approved deferred action status; or (I)
25 has a pending application for adjustment of status to that of an alien
26 lawfully admitted for permanent residence in the United States or
27 conditional permanent resident status in the United States.
28 (3) If an applicant provides evidence of lawful presence set out in
29 subsections (b)(2)(E) through (2)(I), or is an alien lawfully admitted for
30 temporary residence under subsection (b)(2)(B), the division may only
31 issue a driver's license to the person under the following conditions: (A) A
32 driver's license issued pursuant to this subparagraph shall be valid only
33 during the period of time of the applicant's authorized stay in the United
34 States or, if there is no definite end to the period of authorized stay, a
35 period of one year; (B) a driver's license issued pursuant to this
36 subparagraph shall clearly indicate that it is temporary and shall state the
37 date on which it expires; (C) no driver's license issued pursuant to this
38 subparagraph shall be for a longer period of time than the time period
39 permitted by K.S.A. 8-247(a), and amendments thereto; and (D) a driver's
40 license issued pursuant to this subparagraph may be renewed, subject at
41 the time of renewal, to the same requirements and conditions as set out in
42 this subsection (b) for the issuance of the original driver's license.
43 (4) The division shall not issue any driver's license or instruction

