1 permit to any person who is not a resident of the state of Kansas, except as
2 provided in K.S.A. 8-2,148, and amendments thereto.
3 (5) The division shall not issue a driver's license to a person holding a
4 driver's license issued by another state without making reasonable efforts
5 to confirm that the person is terminating or has terminated the driver's
6 license in the other state.
7 (6) The parent or guardian of an applicant under 16 years of age shall
8 sign the application for any driver's license submitted by such applicant.
9 (c) Every application shall state the full legal name, date of birth,
10 gender and address of principal residence of the applicant, and briefly
11 describe the applicant, and shall state whether the applicant has been
12 licensed as a driver prior to such application, and, if so, when and by what
13 state or country. Such application shall state whether any such license has
14 ever been suspended or revoked, or whether an application has ever been
15 refused, and, if so, the date of and reason for such suspension, revocation
16 or refusal. In addition, applications for commercial drivers' licenses and
17 instruction permits for commercial licenses must shall include the
18 following: The applicant's social security number;, the person's signature;
19 and the person's: (1) Digital color image or photograph; or (2) a laser
20 engraved photograph;, certifications, including those required by 49 C.F.R.
21 § 383.71(a), effective January 1, 1991;, a consent to release driving record
22 information; and, any other information required by the division. Each
23 application for a driver's license shall include a question asking if the
24 applicant is willing to give such applicant's authorization to be listed as an
25 organ, eye or tissue donor in the Kansas donor registry in accordance with
26 the revised uniform anatomical gift act, K.S.A. 65-3220 through 65-3244,
27 and amendments thereto. The gift would become effective upon the death
28 of the donor.
29 (d) When an application is received from a person previously licensed
30 in another jurisdiction, the division shall request a copy of the driver's
31 record from the other jurisdiction. When received, the driver's record shall
32 become a part of the driver's record in this state with the same force and
33 effect as though entered on the driver's record in this state in the original
34 instance.
35 (e) When the division receives a request for a driver's record from
36 another licensing jurisdiction the record shall be forwarded without charge.
37 (f) A fee shall be charged as follows:
38 (1) For a class C driver's license issued to a person at least 21 years of
39 age, but less than 65 years of age, $18;
40 (2) for a class C driver's license issued to a person 65 years of age or
41 older, $12;
42 (3) for a class M driver's license issued to a person at least 21 years of
43 age, but less than 65 years of age, $12.50;

