15 If one fails to make an original application or renewal application for a
16 driver's license within the time required by law, or fails to make
17 application within 60 days after becoming a resident of Kansas, a penalty
18 of $1 shall be added to the fee charged for the driver's license.
19 (g) Any person who possesses an identification card as provided in
20 K.S.A. 8-1324, and amendments thereto, shall surrender such
21 identification card to the division upon being issued a valid Kansas driver's
22 license or upon reinstatement and return of a valid Kansas driver's license.
23 (h) The division shall require that any person applying for a driver's
24 license submit to a mandatory facial image capture. The captured facial
25 image shall be displayed on the front of the applicant's driver's license.
26 (i) The director of vehicles may issue a temporary driver's license to
27 an applicant who cannot provide valid documentary evidence as defined
28 by subsection (b)(2), if the applicant provides compelling evidence
29 proving current lawful presence. Any temporary license issued pursuant to
30 this subsection shall be valid for one year.
31 (j) (1) For purposes of this subsection, the division may rely on the
32 division's most recent, existing color digital image and signature image of
33 the applicant for the class C or M driver's license or any class of
34 commercial driver's license if the division has the information on file. The
35 determination on whether an electronic online renewal application or
36 equivalent of a driver's license is permitted shall be made by the director of
37 vehicles or the director's designee. The division shall not renew a driver's
38 license through an electronic online or equivalent process if the license has
39 been previously renewed through an electronic online application in the
40 immediately preceding driver's license period. No renewal under this
41 subsection shall be granted to any person who is:
42 (A) Younger than 30 days from turning 21 years of age;
43 (B) 65 years of age or older;

